-- Iberdrola Unit Receives $150 Million Loan to Upgrade Brazil Grid
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2013-04-08T13:05:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-08/iberdrola-unit-receives-150-million-loan-to-upgrade-brazil-grid.html
Elektro Eletricidade & Servicos SA,
a unit of  Iberdrola SA (IBE)  that distributes power in Brazil, was
awarded a 115 million-euro ($149.8 million) loan by the
European Investment Bank to expand and boost the efficiency of
its grid.  The 12-year loan will be used to upgrade networks in the
states of Sao Paulo and Mato Grosso do Sul, Iberdrola said today
on its website. Bilbao, Spain-based Iberdrola acquired Elektro
in April 2011.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephan Nielsen in Sao Paulo at 
 snielsen8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tina Davis at 
 tinadavis@bloomberg.net  